    "subtype": "equipment",
    "text": "The first of these strips of glittering cloth was worn by a monk from Jinin who would interweave it into his *handwraps of mighty blows*. The spell DC of any spell cast by activating this item is 24. \n* **Armor** You gain a +2 item bonus to saving throws against illusions and Deception checks to Create a Diversion.\n* **Weapon** (visual) After you cast an illusion spell by activating the scarf, the weapon is shrouded in a mesmerizing illusory pattern. Your next Strike causes the target to be confused for 1 round if it hits. If you don't make a Strike by the end of your next turn, the illusion ends with no effect.",
    "traits": [
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 103,
